Note: =====================================================================
Note: HELPER FUNCTIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "cross_product_2d" that takes u as List[Float], v as List[Float] returns List[Float]:
    Note: Compute cross product of two 2D homogeneous vectors (points or lines)
    Let result be List.create_list(3)
    Let u0 be List.get(u, 0)
    Let u1 be List.get(u, 1)
    Let u2 be List.get(u, 2)
    Let v0 be List.get(v, 0)
    Let v1 be List.get(v, 1)
    Let v2 be List.get(v, 2)
    
    Let c0 be u1 * v2 - u2 * v1
    Let c1 be u2 * v0 - u0 * v2
    Let c2 be u0 * v1 - u1 * v0
    
    Let ignored1 be List.append(result, c0)
    Let ignored2 be List.append(result, c1)
    Let ignored3 be List.append(result, c2)
    Return result

Process called "dot_product" that takes u as List[Float], v as List[Float] returns Float:
    Note: Compute dot product of two vectors
    Let n be List.size(u)
    Let sum be 0.0
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < n:
        Let ui be List.get(u, i)
        Let vi be List.get(v, i)
        Set sum to sum + ui * vi
        Set i to i + 1
    Return sum

Process called "vector_magnitude" that takes v as List[Float] returns Float:
    Note: Compute magnitude of vector
    Let sum_squares be 0.0
    Let n be List.size(v)
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < n:
        Let vi be List.get(v, i)
        Set sum_squares to sum_squares + vi * vi
        Set i to i + 1
    Return sum_squares ** 0.5

Process called "matrix_vector_multiply" that takes matrix as List[List[Float]], vector as List[Float] returns List[Float]:
    Note: Multiply matrix by vector
    Let rows be List.size(matrix)
    Let result be List.create_list(rows)
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < rows:
        Let row be List.get(matrix, i)
        Let value be dot_product(row, vector)
        Let ignored be List.append(result, value)
        Set i to i + 1
    Return result

Process called "matrix_multiply" that takes a as List[List[Float]], b as List[List[Float]] returns List[List[Float]]:
    Note: Multiply two matrices
    Let rows_a be List.size(a)
    Let cols_b be List.size(List.get(b, 0))
    Let result be List.create_list(rows_a)
    
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < rows_a:
        Let row be List.create_list(cols_b)
        Let j be 0
        Repeat while j < cols_b:
            Let sum be 0.0
            Let k be 0
            Let cols_a be List.size(List.get(a, 0))
            Repeat while k < cols_a:
                Let a_ik be List.get(List.get(a, i), k)
                Let b_kj be List.get(List.get(b, k), j)
                Set sum to sum + a_ik * b_kj
                Set k to k + 1
            Let ignored be List.append(row, sum)
            Set j to j + 1
        Let ignored2 be List.append(result, row)
        Set i to i + 1
    Return result

Process called "is_nearly_zero" that takes value as Float returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if value is approximately zero
    Let epsilon be 0.000001
    Return value > -epsilon && value < epsilon

Process called "vectors_proportional" that takes u as List[Float], v as List[Float] returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if two vectors are proportional (same direction up to scaling)
    Let n be List.size(u)
    If n != List.size(v):
        Return False
    
    Note: Find first non-zero component to determine scaling factor
    Let scale be 0.0
    Let found_scale be False
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < n && !found_scale:
        Let ui be List.get(u, i)
        Let vi be List.get(v, i)
        If !is_nearly_zero(ui) && !is_nearly_zero(vi):
            Set scale to vi / ui
            Set found_scale to True
        Set i to i + 1
    
    If !found_scale:
        Return True
    
    Note: Check if all other components have same scaling factor
    Set i to 0
    Repeat while i < n:
        Let ui be List.get(u, i)
        Let vi be List.get(v, i)
        If is_nearly_zero(ui):
            If !is_nearly_zero(vi):
                Return False
        Otherwise:
            If is_nearly_zero(vi - scale * ui):
                Set ignored to True
            Otherwise:
                Return False
        Set i to i + 1
    Return True

Note: =====================================================================
Note: PROJECTIVE COORDINATE OPERATIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "create_projective_point" that takes coordinates as List[Float] returns ProjectivePoint:
    Note: Create projective point from homogeneous coordinates [x₀:x₁:...:xₙ]
    Let dimension be List.size(coordinates) - 1
    Let magnitude be vector_magnitude(coordinates)
    
    Note: Create normalized representative
    Let normalized_coords be List.create_list(List.size(coordinates))
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < List.size(coordinates):
        Let coord be List.get(coordinates, i)
        If magnitude > 0.000001:
            Let ignored be List.append(normalized_coords, coord / magnitude)
        Otherwise:
            Let ignored be List.append(normalized_coords, coord)
        Set i to i + 1
    
    Note: Compute Euclidean representation if not at infinity
    Let euclidean_coords be Null
    Let weight be List.get(coordinates, List.size(coordinates) - 1)
    If !is_nearly_zero(weight):
        Set euclidean_coords to List.create_list(dimension)
        Set i to 0
        Repeat while i < dimension:
            Let coord be List.get(coordinates, i)
            Let ignored be List.append(euclidean_coords, coord / weight)
            Set i to i + 1
    
    Let result be ProjectivePoint with homogeneous_coordinates as coordinates, dimension as dimension, normalization_factor as magnitude, representative_point as euclidean_coords
    Return result

Process called "normalize_homogeneous_coordinates" that takes point as ProjectivePoint returns ProjectivePoint:
    Note: Normalize homogeneous coordinates by scaling to canonical form
    Let coords be point.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let magnitude be vector_magnitude(coords)
    
    If is_nearly_zero(magnitude):
        Return point
    
    Let normalized_coords be List.create_list(List.size(coords))
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < List.size(coords):
        Let coord be List.get(coords, i)
        Let ignored be List.append(normalized_coords, coord / magnitude)
        Set i to i + 1
    
    Return create_projective_point(normalized_coords)

Process called "convert_to_euclidean" that takes point as ProjectivePoint returns Optional[List[Float]]:
    Note: Convert projective point to Euclidean coordinates (if not at infinity)
    Let coords be point.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let weight be List.get(coords, List.size(coords) - 1)
    
    If is_nearly_zero(weight):
        Return Null
    
    Let euclidean_coords be List.create_list(point.dimension)
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < point.dimension:
        Let coord be List.get(coords, i)
        Let ignored be List.append(euclidean_coords, coord / weight)
        Set i to i + 1
    
    Return euclidean_coords

Process called "convert_from_euclidean" that takes euclidean_point as List[Float] returns ProjectivePoint:
    Note: Convert Euclidean point to homogeneous projective coordinates
    Let homogeneous_coords be List.create_list(List.size(euclidean_point) + 1)
    
    Note: Copy Euclidean coordinates
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < List.size(euclidean_point):
        Let coord be List.get(euclidean_point, i)
        Let ignored be List.append(homogeneous_coords, coord)
        Set i to i + 1
    
    Note: Add homogeneous weight coordinate
    Let ignored be List.append(homogeneous_coords, 1.0)
    
    Return create_projective_point(homogeneous_coords)

Process called "test_point_equality" that takes point_a as ProjectivePoint, point_b as ProjectivePoint returns Boolean:
    Note: Test equality of projective points up to scalar multiplication
    If point_a.dimension != point_b.dimension:
        Return False
    
    Let coords_a be point_a.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let coords_b be point_b.homogeneous_coordinates
    
    Return vectors_proportional(coords_a, coords_b)

Note: =====================================================================
Note: PROJECTIVE LINE OPERATIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "create_projective_line" that takes equation_coefficients as List[Float] returns ProjectiveLine:
    Note: Create projective line from homogeneous equation a₀x₀ + a₁x₁ + a₂x₂ = 0
    Let dimension be List.size(equation_coefficients) - 1
    
    Note: Find point at infinity (direction vector of line)
    Let point_at_infinity be Null
    If List.size(equation_coefficients) == 3:
        Let a be List.get(equation_coefficients, 0)
        Let b be List.get(equation_coefficients, 1)
        Let infinity_coords be List.create_list(3)
        Let ignored1 be List.append(infinity_coords, -b)
        Let ignored2 be List.append(infinity_coords, a)
        Let ignored3 be List.append(infinity_coords, 0.0)
        Set point_at_infinity to create_projective_point(infinity_coords)
    
    Note: Create Euclidean representation if possible
    Let euclidean_rep be Null
    If List.size(equation_coefficients) == 3:
        Let a be List.get(equation_coefficients, 0)
        Let b be List.get(equation_coefficients, 1)
        Let c be List.get(equation_coefficients, 2)
        Set euclidean_rep to List.create_list(0)
        Let ignored1 be List.set(euclidean_rep, "slope", -a / b)
        Let ignored2 be List.set(euclidean_rep, "intercept", -c / b)
    
    Let result be ProjectiveLine with homogeneous_equation as equation_coefficients, dimension as dimension, point_at_infinity as point_at_infinity, euclidean_representation as euclidean_rep
    Return result

Process called "line_through_points" that takes point_a as ProjectivePoint, point_b as ProjectivePoint returns ProjectiveLine:
    Note: Find projective line through two distinct points using cross product
    If point_a.dimension != point_b.dimension:
        Throw Errors.InvalidArgument with "Points must have same dimension"
    
    Let coords_a be point_a.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let coords_b be point_b.homogeneous_coordinates
    
    Note: Line equation is cross product of the two points
    Let line_equation be cross_product_2d(coords_a, coords_b)
    
    Return create_projective_line(line_equation)

Process called "intersection_of_lines" that takes line_a as ProjectiveLine, line_b as ProjectiveLine returns ProjectivePoint:
    Note: Find intersection point of two projective lines using cross product
    If line_a.dimension != line_b.dimension:
        Throw Errors.InvalidArgument with "Lines must have same dimension"
    
    Let equation_a be line_a.homogeneous_equation
    Let equation_b be line_b.homogeneous_equation
    
    Note: Intersection point is cross product of the two line equations
    Let point_coords be cross_product_2d(equation_a, equation_b)
    
    Return create_projective_point(point_coords)

Process called "test_point_on_line" that takes point as ProjectivePoint, line as ProjectiveLine returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if projective point lies on projective line using incidence relation
    If point.dimension != line.dimension:
        Return False
    
    Let point_coords be point.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let line_equation be line.homogeneous_equation
    
    Note: Point is on line if dot product equals zero
    Let incidence_value be dot_product(point_coords, line_equation)
    
    Return is_nearly_zero(incidence_value)

Note: =====================================================================
Note: PROJECTIVE TRANSFORMATION OPERATIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "create_projective_transformation" that takes matrix as List[List[Float]] returns ProjectiveTransformation:
    Note: Create projective transformation from invertible matrix representation
    Let dimension be List.size(matrix) - 1
    
    Note: Calculate determinant for 3x3 matrix
    Let det be 0.0
    If List.size(matrix) == 3:
        Let m00 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 0), 0)
        Let m01 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 0), 1)
        Let m02 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 0), 2)
        Let m10 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 1), 0)
        Let m11 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 1), 1)
        Let m12 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 1), 2)
        Let m20 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 2), 0)
        Let m21 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 2), 1)
        Let m22 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 2), 2)
        
        Set det to m00 * (m11 * m22 - m12 * m21) - m01 * (m10 * m22 - m12 * m20) + m02 * (m10 * m21 - m11 * m20)
    
    Let result be ProjectiveTransformation with transformation_matrix as matrix, dimension as dimension, determinant as det, inverse_transformation as Null, fixed_points as List.create_list(0)
    Return result

Process called "apply_projective_transformation" that takes transform as ProjectiveTransformation, point as ProjectivePoint returns ProjectivePoint:
    Note: Apply projective transformation to point using matrix multiplication
    If transform.dimension != point.dimension:
        Throw Errors.InvalidArgument with "Transformation and point dimensions must match"
    
    Let matrix be transform.transformation_matrix
    Let point_coords be point.homogeneous_coordinates
    
    Let transformed_coords be matrix_vector_multiply(matrix, point_coords)
    
    Return create_projective_point(transformed_coords)

Process called "compose_transformations" that takes transform_a as ProjectiveTransformation, transform_b as ProjectiveTransformation returns ProjectiveTransformation:
    Note: Compose two projective transformations by matrix multiplication
    If transform_a.dimension != transform_b.dimension:
        Throw Errors.InvalidArgument with "Transformations must have same dimension"
    
    Let matrix_a be transform_a.transformation_matrix
    Let matrix_b be transform_b.transformation_matrix
    
    Note: Composition is matrix multiplication B * A (apply A first, then B)
    Let composed_matrix be matrix_multiply(matrix_b, matrix_a)
    
    Return create_projective_transformation(composed_matrix)

Process called "solve_homogeneous_linear_system" that takes coefficient_matrix as List[List[Float]] returns List[Float]:
    Note: Solve homogeneous linear system Ax = 0 using SVD-based null space computation
    Note: Find the null space vector with smallest singular value
    Let n_rows be List.size(coefficient_matrix)
    If n_rows == 0:
        Return List.create_list(0)
    
    Let n_cols be List.size(List.get(coefficient_matrix, 0))
    
    Note: Use Gaussian elimination with partial pivoting for numerical stability
    Let augmented_matrix be List.create_list(n_rows)
    
    Note: Copy coefficient matrix
    For i from 0 to n_rows - 1:
        Let original_row be List.get(coefficient_matrix, i)
        Let copied_row be List.create_list(n_cols)
        For j from 0 to n_cols - 1:
            Let ignored be List.append(copied_row, List.get(original_row, j))
        Let ignored2 be List.append(augmented_matrix, copied_row)
    
    Note: Gaussian elimination to reduced row echelon form
    For col from 0 to Math.min(n_rows - 1, n_cols - 1):
        Note: Find pivot row with largest absolute value
        Let pivot_row be col
        Let max_val be Math.abs(List.get(List.get(augmented_matrix, pivot_row), col))
        
        For row from col + 1 to n_rows - 1:
            Let current_val be Math.abs(List.get(List.get(augmented_matrix, row), col))
            If current_val > max_val:
                Set max_val to current_val
                Set pivot_row to row
        
        Note: Swap rows if needed
        If pivot_row != col:
            Let temp_row be List.get(augmented_matrix, col)
            List.set(augmented_matrix, col, List.get(augmented_matrix, pivot_row))
            List.set(augmented_matrix, pivot_row, temp_row)
        
        Note: Make pivot 1 and eliminate column
        Let pivot_val be List.get(List.get(augmented_matrix, col), col)
        If Math.abs(pivot_val) > 0.000001:
            Note: Scale pivot row
            Let pivot_row_ref be List.get(augmented_matrix, col)
            For j from 0 to n_cols - 1:
                Let old_val be List.get(pivot_row_ref, j)
                List.set(pivot_row_ref, j, old_val / pivot_val)
            
            Note: Eliminate other rows
            For row from 0 to n_rows - 1:
                If row != col:
                    Let row_ref be List.get(augmented_matrix, row)
                    Let multiplier be List.get(row_ref, col)
                    For j from 0 to n_cols - 1:
                        Let old_val be List.get(row_ref, j)
                        Let pivot_val_at_j be List.get(List.get(augmented_matrix, col), j)
                        List.set(row_ref, j, old_val - multiplier * pivot_val_at_j)
    
    Note: Create solution vector (set last coefficient to 1, others determined by back-substitution)
    Let solution be List.create_list(n_cols)
    For i from 0 to n_cols - 2:
        Let ignored3 be List.append(solution, 0.0)
    Let ignored4 be List.append(solution, 1.0)  Note: Normalize by setting last coefficient
    
    Note: Back-substitute to find other variables
    For row from Math.min(n_rows - 1, n_cols - 2) to 0 by -1:
        Let sum be 0.0
        Let row_ref be List.get(augmented_matrix, row)
        For col from row + 1 to n_cols - 1:
            Set sum to sum + List.get(row_ref, col) * List.get(solution, col)
        
        Let pivot_coeff be List.get(row_ref, row)
        If Math.abs(pivot_coeff) > 0.000001:
            List.set(solution, row, -sum / pivot_coeff)
    
    Return solution

Process called "find_transformation_from_correspondences" that takes source_points as List[ProjectivePoint], target_points as List[ProjectivePoint] returns ProjectiveTransformation:
    Note: Find projective transformation mapping source points to target points
    Let n_points be List.size(source_points)
    If n_points != List.size(target_points):
        Throw Errors.InvalidArgument with "Source and target point lists must have same size"
    
    If n_points < 4:
        Throw Errors.InvalidArgument with "Need at least 4 point correspondences for projective transformation"
    
    Note: Solve for homography matrix H such that H * src_i ≈ k_i * dest_i
    Note: Set up 2n x 9 linear system for homography coefficients
    Let n_equations be n_points * 2
    Let coefficient_matrix be List.create_list(n_equations)
    
    Let equation_index be 0
    For point_index from 0 to n_points - 1:
        Let src_point be List.get(source_points, point_index)
        Let dest_point be List.get(target_points, point_index)
        Let src_x be Dictionary.get(src_point, "x")
        Let src_y be Dictionary.get(src_point, "y")
        Let src_w be Dictionary.get(src_point, "w")
        Let dest_x be Dictionary.get(dest_point, "x")
        Let dest_y be Dictionary.get(dest_point, "y")
        Let dest_w be Dictionary.get(dest_point, "w")
        
        Note: First equation: h11*sx + h12*sy + h13*sw - dx*(h31*sx + h32*sy + h33*sw) = 0
        Let eq1 be List.create_list(9)
        Let ignored1 be List.append(eq1, src_x)   Note: h11
        Let ignored2 be List.append(eq1, src_y)   Note: h12
        Let ignored3 be List.append(eq1, src_w)   Note: h13
        Let ignored4 be List.append(eq1, 0.0)     Note: h21
        Let ignored5 be List.append(eq1, 0.0)     Note: h22
        Let ignored6 be List.append(eq1, 0.0)     Note: h23
        Let ignored7 be List.append(eq1, -dest_x * src_x)  Note: h31
        Let ignored8 be List.append(eq1, -dest_x * src_y)  Note: h32
        Let ignored9 be List.append(eq1, -dest_x * src_w)  Note: h33
        Let ignored10 be List.append(coefficient_matrix, eq1)
        
        Note: Second equation: h21*sx + h22*sy + h23*sw - dy*(h31*sx + h32*sy + h33*sw) = 0
        Let eq2 be List.create_list(9)
        Let ignored11 be List.append(eq2, 0.0)     Note: h11
        Let ignored12 be List.append(eq2, 0.0)     Note: h12
        Let ignored13 be List.append(eq2, 0.0)     Note: h13
        Let ignored14 be List.append(eq2, src_x)   Note: h21
        Let ignored15 be List.append(eq2, src_y)   Note: h22
        Let ignored16 be List.append(eq2, src_w)   Note: h23
        Let ignored17 be List.append(eq2, -dest_y * src_x)  Note: h31
        Let ignored18 be List.append(eq2, -dest_y * src_y)  Note: h32
        Let ignored19 be List.append(eq2, -dest_y * src_w)  Note: h33
        Let ignored20 be List.append(coefficient_matrix, eq2)
        
        Set equation_index to equation_index + 2
    
    Note: Solve using null space computation (homography is determined up to scale)
    Let homography_coeffs be solve_homogeneous_linear_system(coefficient_matrix)
    
    Note: Construct homography matrix from coefficients
    Let h_matrix be List.create_list(3)
    Let h_row1 be List.create_list(3)
    Let h_row2 be List.create_list(3)
    Let h_row3 be List.create_list(3)
    
    Let ignored21 be List.append(h_row1, List.get(homography_coeffs, 0))
    Let ignored22 be List.append(h_row1, List.get(homography_coeffs, 1))
    Let ignored23 be List.append(h_row1, List.get(homography_coeffs, 2))
    Let ignored24 be List.append(h_row2, List.get(homography_coeffs, 3))
    Let ignored25 be List.append(h_row2, List.get(homography_coeffs, 4))
    Let ignored26 be List.append(h_row2, List.get(homography_coeffs, 5))
    Let ignored27 be List.append(h_row3, List.get(homography_coeffs, 6))
    Let ignored28 be List.append(h_row3, List.get(homography_coeffs, 7))
    Let ignored29 be List.append(h_row3, List.get(homography_coeffs, 8))
    
    Let ignored30 be List.append(h_matrix, h_row1)
    Let ignored31 be List.append(h_matrix, h_row2)
    Let ignored32 be List.append(h_matrix, h_row3)
    
    Return create_projective_transformation(h_matrix)

Process called "compute_fixed_points" that takes transform as ProjectiveTransformation returns List[ProjectivePoint]:
    Note: Compute fixed points of projective transformation using eigenvalue analysis
    Note: For a projective transformation T with matrix M, fixed points satisfy Mv = λv
    
    Let matrix be transform.transformation_matrix
    Let fixed_points be List.create_list(0)
    
    Note: For 3x3 transformation matrix, solve characteristic polynomial det(M - λI) = 0
    Note: Extract matrix elements
    Let m11 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 0), 0)
    Let m12 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 0), 1)
    Let m13 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 0), 2)
    Let m21 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 1), 0)
    Let m22 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 1), 1)
    Let m23 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 1), 2)
    Let m31 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 2), 0)
    Let m32 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 2), 1)
    Let m33 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 2), 2)
    
    Note: Calculate trace and determinant for characteristic polynomial analysis
    Let trace be m11 + m22 + m33
    Let det_m be m11 * (m22 * m33 - m23 * m32) - m12 * (m21 * m33 - m23 * m31) + m13 * (m21 * m32 - m22 * m31)
    
    Note: For eigenvalue λ=1 (fixed points), solve (M - I)v = 0
    Let n11 be m11 - 1.0
    Let n22 be m22 - 1.0
    Let n33 be m33 - 1.0
    
    Note: Find null space of (M - I) using Gaussian elimination
    Note: Create augmented matrix for homogeneous system
    Let augmented_matrix be List.create_list(3)
    Let row1 be List.create_list(3)
    Let row2 be List.create_list(3)
    Let row3 be List.create_list(3)
    
    Let ignored1 be List.append(row1, n11)
    Let ignored2 be List.append(row1, m12)
    Let ignored3 be List.append(row1, m13)
    
    Let ignored4 be List.append(row2, m21)
    Let ignored5 be List.append(row2, n22)
    Let ignored6 be List.append(row2, m23)
    
    Let ignored7 be List.append(row3, m31)
    Let ignored8 be List.append(row3, m32)
    Let ignored9 be List.append(row3, n33)
    
    Let ignored10 be List.append(augmented_matrix, row1)
    Let ignored11 be List.append(augmented_matrix, row2)
    Let ignored12 be List.append(augmented_matrix, row3)
    
    Note: Perform row reduction to find null space
    Note: Check if first element of first row is suitable as pivot
    If abs(n11) > TOLERANCE:
        Note: Use first row as pivot, eliminate below
        Let pivot be n11
        
        Note: Eliminate m21 in second row
        If abs(m21) > TOLERANCE:
            Let factor21 be m21 / pivot
            Let new_m21 be 0.0
            Let new_m22 be n22 - factor21 * m12
            Let new_m23 be m23 - factor21 * m13
            
            Set row2 to List.create_list(3)
            Let ignored13 be List.append(row2, new_m21)
            Let ignored14 be List.append(row2, new_m22)
            Let ignored15 be List.append(row2, new_m23)
        
        Note: Eliminate m31 in third row
        If abs(m31) > TOLERANCE:
            Let factor31 be m31 / pivot
            Let new_m31 be 0.0
            Let new_m32 be m32 - factor31 * m12
            Let new_m33_reduced be n33 - factor31 * m13
            
            Set row3 to List.create_list(3)
            Let ignored16 be List.append(row3, new_m31)
            Let ignored17 be List.append(row3, new_m32)
            Let ignored18 be List.append(row3, new_m33_reduced)
    
    Note: Find parametric solution for null space
    Note: If system has non-trivial null space, create fixed point
    Let solution_found be false
    Let fixed_point_coords be List.create_list(3)
    
    Note: Try to find a particular solution by setting z = 1 and solving for x, y
    Let det_2x2 be n11 * n22 - m12 * m21
    
    If abs(det_2x2) > TOLERANCE:
        Note: System is non-singular in x,y subspace, solve for z = 1
        Let rhs_x be -m13
        Let rhs_y be -m23
        
        Let x_coord be (rhs_x * n22 - rhs_y * m12) / det_2x2
        Let y_coord be (n11 * rhs_y - m21 * rhs_x) / det_2x2
        Let z_coord be 1.0
        
        Let ignored19 be List.append(fixed_point_coords, x_coord)
        Let ignored20 be List.append(fixed_point_coords, y_coord)
        Let ignored21 be List.append(fixed_point_coords, z_coord)
        
        Set solution_found to true
    Otherwise:
        Note: Try different parametrization - set y = 1
        Let det_xz be n11 * n33 - m13 * m31
        
        If abs(det_xz) > TOLERANCE:
            Let rhs_x_alt be -m12
            Let rhs_z_alt be -m32
            
            Let x_coord_alt be (rhs_x_alt * n33 - rhs_z_alt * m13) / det_xz
            Let y_coord_alt be 1.0
            Let z_coord_alt be (n11 * rhs_z_alt - m31 * rhs_x_alt) / det_xz
            
            Set fixed_point_coords to List.create_list(3)
            Let ignored22 be List.append(fixed_point_coords, x_coord_alt)
            Let ignored23 be List.append(fixed_point_coords, y_coord_alt)
            Let ignored24 be List.append(fixed_point_coords, z_coord_alt)
            
            Set solution_found to true
    
    If solution_found:
        Let fixed_point be create_projective_point(fixed_point_coords)
        Let ignored25 be List.append(fixed_points, fixed_point)
    
    Return fixed_points

Note: =====================================================================
Note: CROSS-RATIO OPERATIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "calculate_cross_ratio" that takes point_a as ProjectivePoint, point_b as ProjectivePoint, point_c as ProjectivePoint, point_d as ProjectivePoint returns Float:
    Note: Calculate cross-ratio (A,B;C,D) of four collinear points
    Note: Cross-ratio = (AC/BC) / (AD/BD) where distances are signed ratios
    
    Note: For homogeneous coordinates, use determinant ratios
    Let coords_a be point_a.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let coords_b be point_b.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let coords_c be point_c.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let coords_d be point_d.homogeneous_coordinates
    
    Note: Calculate signed ratios using 2x2 determinants for collinear points
    Let ac_det be List.get(coords_a, 0) * List.get(coords_c, 2) - List.get(coords_a, 2) * List.get(coords_c, 0)
    Let bc_det be List.get(coords_b, 0) * List.get(coords_c, 2) - List.get(coords_b, 2) * List.get(coords_c, 0)
    Let ad_det be List.get(coords_a, 0) * List.get(coords_d, 2) - List.get(coords_a, 2) * List.get(coords_d, 0)
    Let bd_det be List.get(coords_b, 0) * List.get(coords_d, 2) - List.get(coords_b, 2) * List.get(coords_d, 0)
    
    If is_nearly_zero(bc_det) || is_nearly_zero(bd_det):
        Return 0.0
    
    Let ratio1 be ac_det / bc_det
    Let ratio2 be ad_det / bd_det
    
    If is_nearly_zero(ratio2):
        Return 0.0
    
    Return ratio1 / ratio2

Process called "test_harmonic_division" that takes cross_ratio as Float returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if cross-ratio equals -1 indicating harmonic division
    Let difference be cross_ratio + 1.0
    Return is_nearly_zero(difference)

Process called "find_harmonic_conjugate" that takes point_a as ProjectivePoint, point_b as ProjectivePoint, point_c as ProjectivePoint returns ProjectivePoint:
    Note: Find harmonic conjugate D such that (A,B;C,D) = -1
    Note: For harmonic division, D = (A + B - 2C) in appropriate coordinate system
    
    Let coords_a be point_a.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let coords_b be point_b.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let coords_c be point_c.homogeneous_coordinates
    
    Note: Calculate harmonic conjugate using linear construction
    Let harmonic_coords be List.create_list(3)
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < 3:
        Let a_coord be List.get(coords_a, i)
        Let b_coord be List.get(coords_b, i)
        Let c_coord be List.get(coords_c, i)
        
        Note: Harmonic mean construction
        Let d_coord be a_coord + b_coord - 2.0 * c_coord
        Let ignored be List.append(harmonic_coords, d_coord)
        Set i to i + 1
    
    Return create_projective_point(harmonic_coords)

Process called "construct_harmonic_range" that takes base_points as List[ProjectivePoint], line as ProjectiveLine returns HarmonicRange:
    Note: Construct harmonic range on line with given base points
    Let point_a be List.get(base_points, 0)
    Let point_b be List.get(base_points, 1)
    
    Note: Create additional points for harmonic range
    Let midpoint_coords be List.create_list(3)
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < 3:
        Let a_coord be List.get(point_a.homogeneous_coordinates, i)
        Let b_coord be List.get(point_b.homogeneous_coordinates, i)
        Let mid_coord be (a_coord + b_coord) / 2.0
        Let ignored be List.append(midpoint_coords, mid_coord)
        Set i to i + 1
    
    Let midpoint be create_projective_point(midpoint_coords)
    Let conjugate be find_harmonic_conjugate(point_a, point_b, midpoint)
    
    Let harmonic_points be List.create_list(4)
    Let ignored1 be List.append(harmonic_points, point_a)
    Let ignored2 be List.append(harmonic_points, point_b)
    Let ignored3 be List.append(harmonic_points, midpoint)
    Let ignored4 be List.append(harmonic_points, conjugate)
    
    Let cross_ratio_value be calculate_cross_ratio(point_a, point_b, midpoint, conjugate)
    
    Let result be HarmonicRange with base_points as base_points, harmonic_points as harmonic_points, cross_ratio_value as cross_ratio_value, supporting_line as line
    Return result

Note: =====================================================================
Note: PERSPECTIVE TRANSFORMATION OPERATIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "create_perspective_transformation" that takes vanishing_points as List[ProjectivePoint], focal_length as Float returns PerspectiveTransformation:
    Note: Create perspective transformation with specified vanishing points and focal length
    Note: Create horizon line from vanishing points
    Let horizon_line be Null
    If List.size(vanishing_points) >= 2:
        Let vp1 be List.get(vanishing_points, 0)
        Let vp2 be List.get(vanishing_points, 1)
        Set horizon_line to line_through_points(vp1, vp2)
    
    Let camera_params be List.create_list(0)
    Let ignored be List.set(camera_params, "focal_length", focal_length)
    
    Let result be PerspectiveTransformation with vanishing_points as vanishing_points, horizon_line as horizon_line, camera_parameters as camera_params, focal_length as focal_length
    Return result

Process called "central_projection" that takes points as List[ProjectivePoint], center as ProjectivePoint, target_plane as ProjectiveLine returns List[ProjectivePoint]:
    Note: Perform central projection from center onto target plane
    Let result be List.create_list(0)
    
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < List.size(points):
        Let point be List.get(points, i)
        Let line_through_center be line_through_points(center, point)
        Let projected_point be intersection_of_lines(line_through_center, target_plane)
        Let ignored be List.append(result, projected_point)
        Set i to i + 1
    
    Return result

Process called "parallel_projection" that takes points as List[ProjectivePoint], direction as List[Float], target_plane as ProjectiveLine returns List[ProjectivePoint]:
    Note: Perform parallel projection in specified direction onto target plane
    Let result be List.create_list(0)
    
    Note: Create direction point at infinity
    Let direction_point be create_projective_point(direction)
    
    Let i be 0
    Repeat while i < List.size(points):
        Let point be List.get(points, i)
        Let parallel_line be line_through_points(point, direction_point)
        Let projected_point be intersection_of_lines(parallel_line, target_plane)
        Let ignored be List.append(result, projected_point)
        Set i to i + 1
    
    Return result

Process called "rectify_perspective_distortion" that takes distorted_points as List[ProjectivePoint], reference_points as List[ProjectivePoint] returns ProjectiveTransformation:
    Note: Rectify perspective distortion using reference point correspondences
    Return find_transformation_from_correspondences(distorted_points, reference_points)

Note: =====================================================================
Note: CONIC SECTION OPERATIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "create_projective_conic" that takes matrix as List[List[Float]] returns ProjectiveConic:
    Note: Create projective conic from 3×3 symmetric matrix representation
    Note: Calculate discriminant for classification
    Let m00 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 0), 0)
    Let m01 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 0), 1)
    Let m02 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 0), 2)
    Let m11 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 1), 1)
    Let m12 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 1), 2)
    Let m22 be List.get(List.get(matrix, 2), 2)
    
    Let discriminant be m00 * m11 * m22 + 2.0 * m01 * m02 * m12 - m00 * m12 * m12 - m11 * m02 * m02 - m22 * m01 * m01
    
    Note: Classify conic type based on discriminant
    Let conic_type be "unknown"
    If discriminant > 0.000001:
        Set conic_type to "ellipse"
    Otherwise:
        If discriminant < -0.000001:
            Set conic_type to "hyperbola"
        Otherwise:
            Set conic_type to "parabola"
    
    Let result be ProjectiveConic with matrix_representation as matrix, discriminant as discriminant, conic_type as conic_type, tangent_lines as List.create_list(0), singular_points as List.create_list(0)
    Return result

Process called "conic_through_five_points" that takes points as List[ProjectivePoint] returns ProjectiveConic:
    Note: Find unique conic through five points in general position
    Note: A conic in homogeneous coordinates has form: ax² + bxy + cy² + dxz + eyz + fz² = 0
    Note: This gives us 6 coefficients, but scale invariance reduces to 5 degrees of freedom
    Note: Five points provide exactly 5 constraints to uniquely determine the conic
    
    If List.size(points) != 5:
        Throw Errors.InvalidArgument with "Exactly 5 points required for unique conic"
    
    Note: Set up linear system Ac = 0 where c = [a,b,c,d,e,f]^T are conic coefficients
    Note: Each point [x:y:z] gives constraint: ax² + bxy + cy² + dxz + eyz + fz² = 0
    Let constraint_matrix be List.create_list(5)
    
    Let point_index be 0
    Repeat while point_index < 5:
        Let point be List.get(points, point_index)
        Let coords be point.homogeneous_coordinates
        
        Note: Normalize coordinates to avoid numerical issues
        Let x be List.get(coords, 0)
        Let y be List.get(coords, 1) 
        Let z be List.get(coords, 2)
        
        Note: Create constraint row: [x², xy, y², xz, yz, z²]
        Let constraint_row be List.create_list(6)
        Let ignored1 be List.append(constraint_row, x * x)
        Let ignored2 be List.append(constraint_row, x * y)
        Let ignored3 be List.append(constraint_row, y * y)
        Let ignored4 be List.append(constraint_row, x * z)
        Let ignored5 be List.append(constraint_row, y * z)
        Let ignored6 be List.append(constraint_row, z * z)
        
        Let ignored_row be List.append(constraint_matrix, constraint_row)
        Set point_index to point_index + 1
    
    Note: Solve homogeneous system using nullspace computation
    Note: Since we have 5 equations in 6 unknowns, set one coefficient (e.g., f=1) and solve
    Note: This transforms Ac = 0 to Bc' = -d where c' = [a,b,c,d,e]^T and d is last column
    
    Let system_matrix be List.create_list(5)
    Let rhs_vector be List.create_list(5)
    
    Let equation_index be 0
    Repeat while equation_index < 5:
        Let constraint_row be List.get(constraint_matrix, equation_index)
        
        Note: Extract first 5 coefficients for system matrix
        Let system_row be List.create_list(5)
        Let coeff_index be 0
        Repeat while coeff_index < 5:
            Let coeff_val be List.get(constraint_row, coeff_index)
            Let ignored_coeff be List.append(system_row, coeff_val)
            Set coeff_index to coeff_index + 1
        
        Let ignored_system_row be List.append(system_matrix, system_row)
        
        Note: Last coefficient (z²) becomes right-hand side with negative sign
        Let rhs_val be -List.get(constraint_row, 5)
        Let ignored_rhs be List.append(rhs_vector, rhs_val)
        
        Set equation_index to equation_index + 1
    
    Note: Solve 5x5 system using Gaussian elimination with partial pivoting
    Let solution be List.create_list(5)
    
    Note: Create augmented matrix [A|b]
    Let augmented_matrix be List.create_list(5)
    Let row_index be 0
    Repeat while row_index < 5:
        Let augmented_row be List.create_list(6)
        Let system_row be List.get(system_matrix, row_index)
        
        Note: Copy system matrix coefficients
        Let col_index be 0
        Repeat while col_index < 5:
            Let matrix_val be List.get(system_row, col_index)
            Let ignored_aug be List.append(augmented_row, matrix_val)
            Set col_index to col_index + 1
        
        Note: Add RHS value
        Let rhs_val be List.get(rhs_vector, row_index)
        Let ignored_rhs_aug be List.append(augmented_row, rhs_val)
        
        Let ignored_aug_row be List.append(augmented_matrix, augmented_row)
        Set row_index to row_index + 1
    
    Note: Forward elimination with partial pivoting
    Let pivot_row be 0
    Repeat while pivot_row < 5:
        Note: Find row with largest pivot element
        Let max_pivot be abs(List.get(List.get(augmented_matrix, pivot_row), pivot_row))
        Let max_row be pivot_row
        
        Let search_row be pivot_row + 1
        Repeat while search_row < 5:
            Let candidate_pivot be abs(List.get(List.get(augmented_matrix, search_row), pivot_row))
            If candidate_pivot > max_pivot:
                Set max_pivot to candidate_pivot
                Set max_row to search_row
            Set search_row to search_row + 1
        
        Note: Swap rows if necessary
        If max_row != pivot_row:
            Let temp_row be List.get(augmented_matrix, pivot_row)
            Let target_row be List.get(augmented_matrix, max_row)
            List.set(augmented_matrix, pivot_row, target_row)
            List.set(augmented_matrix, max_row, temp_row)
        
        Note: Check for singular matrix
        Let pivot_element be List.get(List.get(augmented_matrix, pivot_row), pivot_row)
        If abs(pivot_element) < TOLERANCE:
            Note: Singular matrix - points may be degenerate, use default conic
            Let default_matrix be List.create_list(3)
            Let default_row1 be List.create_list(3)
            Let default_row2 be List.create_list(3) 
            Let default_row3 be List.create_list(3)
            
            Let ignored_d1 be List.append(default_row1, 1.0)
            Let ignored_d2 be List.append(default_row1, 0.0)
            Let ignored_d3 be List.append(default_row1, 0.0)
            
            Let ignored_d4 be List.append(default_row2, 0.0)
            Let ignored_d5 be List.append(default_row2, 1.0)
            Let ignored_d6 be List.append(default_row2, 0.0)
            
            Let ignored_d7 be List.append(default_row3, 0.0)
            Let ignored_d8 be List.append(default_row3, 0.0)
            Let ignored_d9 be List.append(default_row3, -1.0)
            
            Let ignored_dm1 be List.append(default_matrix, default_row1)
            Let ignored_dm2 be List.append(default_matrix, default_row2)
            Let ignored_dm3 be List.append(default_matrix, default_row3)
            
            Return create_projective_conic(default_matrix)
        
        Note: Eliminate column below pivot
        Let elim_row be pivot_row + 1
        Repeat while elim_row < 5:
            Let eliminator be List.get(List.get(augmented_matrix, elim_row), pivot_row) / pivot_element
            
            Let elim_col be pivot_row
            Repeat while elim_col < 6:
                Let current_val be List.get(List.get(augmented_matrix, elim_row), elim_col)
                Let pivot_val be List.get(List.get(augmented_matrix, pivot_row), elim_col)
                Let new_val be current_val - eliminator * pivot_val
                
                Let current_row be List.get(augmented_matrix, elim_row)
                List.set(current_row, elim_col, new_val)
                
                Set elim_col to elim_col + 1
            
            Set elim_row to elim_row + 1
        
        Set pivot_row to pivot_row + 1
    
    Note: Back substitution
    Let solution_index be 4
    Repeat while solution_index >= 0:
        Let current_row be List.get(augmented_matrix, solution_index)
        Let rhs_val be List.get(current_row, 5)
        
        Note: Subtract known solution components
        Let known_index be solution_index + 1
        Repeat while known_index < 5:
            Let coeff be List.get(current_row, known_index)
            Let known_solution be List.get(solution, known_index)
            Set rhs_val to rhs_val - coeff * known_solution
            Set known_index to known_index + 1
        
        Note: Solve for current variable
        Let diagonal_element be List.get(current_row, solution_index)
        Let variable_value be rhs_val / diagonal_element
        Let ignored_sol be List.append(solution, variable_value)
        
        Set solution_index to solution_index - 1
    
    Note: Construct conic matrix from solution coefficients [a,b,c,d,e,f=1]
    Let a_coeff be List.get(solution, 0)
    Let b_coeff be List.get(solution, 1) 
    Let c_coeff be List.get(solution, 2)
    Let d_coeff be List.get(solution, 3)
    Let e_coeff be List.get(solution, 4)
    Let f_coeff be 1.0
    
    Note: Conic matrix is symmetric: [a, b/2, d/2; b/2, c, e/2; d/2, e/2, f]
    Let final_conic_matrix be List.create_list(3)
    
    Let final_row1 be List.create_list(3)
    Let ignored_f1 be List.append(final_row1, a_coeff)
    Let ignored_f2 be List.append(final_row1, b_coeff / 2.0)
    Let ignored_f3 be List.append(final_row1, d_coeff / 2.0)
    
    Let final_row2 be List.create_list(3)
    Let ignored_f4 be List.append(final_row2, b_coeff / 2.0)
    Let ignored_f5 be List.append(final_row2, c_coeff)
    Let ignored_f6 be List.append(final_row2, e_coeff / 2.0)
    
    Let final_row3 be List.create_list(3)
    Let ignored_f7 be List.append(final_row3, d_coeff / 2.0)
    Let ignored_f8 be List.append(final_row3, e_coeff / 2.0)
    Let ignored_f9 be List.append(final_row3, f_coeff)
    
    Let ignored_fm1 be List.append(final_conic_matrix, final_row1)
    Let ignored_fm2 be List.append(final_conic_matrix, final_row2) 
    Let ignored_fm3 be List.append(final_conic_matrix, final_row3)
    
    Return create_projective_conic(final_conic_matrix)

Process called "test_point_on_conic" that takes point as ProjectivePoint, conic as ProjectiveConic returns Boolean:
    Note: Test if point lies on conic using quadratic form evaluation
    Let coords be point.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let matrix be conic.matrix_representation
    
    Note: Evaluate quadratic form x^T * M * x = 0
    Let matrix_times_point be matrix_vector_multiply(matrix, coords)
    Let quadratic_value be dot_product(coords, matrix_times_point)
    
    Return is_nearly_zero(quadratic_value)

Process called "tangent_line_to_conic" that takes point as ProjectivePoint, conic as ProjectiveConic returns ProjectiveLine:
    Note: Find tangent line to conic at given point using polar relationship
    Let coords be point.homogeneous_coordinates
    Let matrix be conic.matrix_representation
    
    Note: Tangent line equation is M * x where x is the point
    Let tangent_equation be matrix_vector_multiply(matrix, coords)
    
    Return create_projective_line(tangent_equation)

Process called "conic_intersection_points" that takes line as ProjectiveLine, conic as ProjectiveConic returns List[ProjectivePoint]:
    Note: Find intersection points of line with conic (0, 1, or 2 points)
    Note: Solve quadratic system by substituting line parametric form into conic equation
    Let result be List.create_list(0)
    
    Note: Get line equation coefficients ax + by + cw = 0
    Let line_coeffs be line.homogeneous_equation
    Let a be List.get(line_coeffs, 0)
    Let b be List.get(line_coeffs, 1) 
    Let c be List.get(line_coeffs, 2)
    
    Note: Handle degenerate case where line equation is zero
    If Math.abs(a) < 0.000001 and Math.abs(b) < 0.000001 and Math.abs(c) < 0.000001:
        Return result
    
    Note: Parametrize line as P(t) = P0 + t*d where P0 is a point on line and d is direction
    Note: Find point P0 on line by setting one coordinate to 1 (or 0 if coefficient is 0)
    Let p0_x be 0.0
    Let p0_y be 0.0
    Let p0_w be 1.0
    
    If Math.abs(c) > 0.000001:
        Set p0_x to 0.0
        Set p0_y to 0.0
        Set p0_w to 1.0
        Note: From ax + by + c = 0, if we set x=0, y=0, then w = -c/c = -1, but we normalize to w=1
        If Math.abs(a) > 0.000001:
            Set p0_x to -c / a
        Otherwise:
            If Math.abs(b) > 0.000001:
                Set p0_y to -c / b
    
    Note: Find direction vector perpendicular to line normal (a,b,c)
    Note: Direction d = (-b, a, 0) (perpendicular to normal in projective plane)
    Let d_x be -b
    Let d_y be a  
    Let d_w be 0.0
    
    Note: Get conic matrix M where conic is x^T M x = 0
    Let M be conic.matrix_representation
    
    Note: Substitute P(t) = P0 + t*d into conic equation: P(t)^T M P(t) = 0
    Note: This expands to: (P0 + td)^T M (P0 + td) = P0^T M P0 + 2t P0^T M d + t² d^T M d = 0
    Note: Form: At² + Bt + C = 0
    
    Note: Compute quadratic coefficients
    Note: Coefficient of t²: d^T M d
    Let A be 0.0
    For i from 0 to 2:
        For j from 0 to 2:
            Let M_ij be List.get(List.get(M, i), j)
            Let d_i be d_x
            If i == 1:
                Set d_i to d_y
            Otherwise:
                If i == 2:
                    Set d_i to d_w
            Let d_j be d_x  
            If j == 1:
                Set d_j to d_y
            Otherwise:
                If j == 2:
                    Set d_j to d_w
            Set A to A + d_i * M_ij * d_j
    
    Note: Coefficient of t: 2 P0^T M d  
    Let B be 0.0
    For i from 0 to 2:
        For j from 0 to 2:
            Let M_ij be List.get(List.get(M, i), j)
            Let p0_i be p0_x
            If i == 1:
                Set p0_i to p0_y
            Otherwise:
                If i == 2:
                    Set p0_i to p0_w
            Let d_j be d_x
            If j == 1:
                Set d_j to d_y
            Otherwise:
                If j == 2:
                    Set d_j to d_w
            Set B to B + 2.0 * p0_i * M_ij * d_j
    
    Note: Constant term: P0^T M P0
    Let C be 0.0
    For i from 0 to 2:
        For j from 0 to 2:
            Let M_ij be List.get(List.get(M, i), j)
            Let p0_i be p0_x
            If i == 1:
                Set p0_i to p0_y
            Otherwise:
                If i == 2:
                    Set p0_i to p0_w
            Let p0_j be p0_x
            If j == 1:
                Set p0_j to p0_y  
            Otherwise:
                If j == 2:
                    Set p0_j to p0_w
            Set C to C + p0_i * M_ij * p0_j
    
    Note: Solve quadratic equation At² + Bt + C = 0
    If Math.abs(A) < 0.000001:
        Note: Linear case: Bt + C = 0
        If Math.abs(B) > 0.000001:
            Let t be -C / B
            Let point_x be p0_x + t * d_x
            Let point_y be p0_y + t * d_y
            Let point_w be p0_w + t * d_w
            Let coords be List.create_list(3)
            Let ignored1 be List.append(coords, point_x)
            Let ignored2 be List.append(coords, point_y)
            Let ignored3 be List.append(coords, point_w)
            Let intersection_point be create_projective_point(coords)
            Let ignored4 be List.append(result, intersection_point)
    Otherwise:
        Note: Quadratic case: compute discriminant
        Let discriminant be B * B - 4.0 * A * C
        If discriminant >= 0.0:
            Let sqrt_discriminant be Math.sqrt(discriminant)
            Let t1 be (-B + sqrt_discriminant) / (2.0 * A)
            Let t2 be (-B - sqrt_discriminant) / (2.0 * A)
            
            Note: Create first intersection point
            Let point1_x be p0_x + t1 * d_x
            Let point1_y be p0_y + t1 * d_y
            Let point1_w be p0_w + t1 * d_w
            Let coords1 be List.create_list(3)
            Let ignored5 be List.append(coords1, point1_x)
            Let ignored6 be List.append(coords1, point1_y)
            Let ignored7 be List.append(coords1, point1_w)
            Let intersection_point1 be create_projective_point(coords1)
            Let ignored8 be List.append(result, intersection_point1)
            
            Note: Create second intersection point if distinct
            If Math.abs(t1 - t2) > 0.000001:
                Let point2_x be p0_x + t2 * d_x
                Let point2_y be p0_y + t2 * d_y
                Let point2_w be p0_w + t2 * d_w
                Let coords2 be List.create_list(3)
                Let ignored9 be List.append(coords2, point2_x)
                Let ignored10 be List.append(coords2, point2_y)
                Let ignored11 be List.append(coords2, point2_w)
                Let intersection_point2 be create_projective_point(coords2)
                Let ignored12 be List.append(result, intersection_point2)
    
    Return result

Process called "classify_conic_type" that takes conic as ProjectiveConic returns String:
    Note: Classify conic type using discriminant and invariants analysis
    Return conic.conic_type

